The paper focuses on improving object detection performance, specifically on small objects, using data augmentation techniques. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The proposed method involves oversampling and copy-pasting small objects, which can be considered as a form of data augmentation, and thus, the paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO) categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on a popular dataset, MS COCO, which is commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
